WEBVTT

00:02.120 --> 00:08.980
One of Aoi Ashito's biggest weaknesses is
 how narrow the scope of his soccer is.

00:09.650 --> 00:11.860
He views it all at the individual level.

00:12.110 --> 00:14.550
"<i>I</i> will lead the team."

00:14.870 --> 00:17.150
"<i>I</i> will get all the good chances."

00:17.150 --> 00:20.430
It's always "I" this, or "I" that, or "I" the other.

00:21.510 --> 00:28.130
A classic example of a player unable to
 think beyond his own game. However...

00:28.890 --> 00:31.630
The fundamental shape 
in soccer is the triangle.

00:32.130 --> 00:34.790
It takes at least three 
players to do anything.

02:07.730 --> 02:12.730
What? Is he trying to buy 
time again because we scored?

02:13.090 --> 02:16.490
Hey, shit heel! Ya seriously 
wantin' me to snap your neck?!

02:25.320 --> 02:30.120
In the 11-on-21 game, 
you said something to us.

02:30.690 --> 02:32.750
"Let's focus on the basics."

02:35.370 --> 02:36.530
I did.

02:37.580 --> 02:41.760
In that training game, all we were
 doing was relying on numbers,

02:41.760 --> 02:44.010
so your words resonated with us.

02:44.790 --> 02:49.390
In actual fact, the point of the 
exercise wasn't about numbers.

02:49.390 --> 02:55.960
It was about whether we could play the game
 properly, whatever the number of players.

02:56.780 --> 03:00.200
And the fundamental shape
 in soccer is the triangle.

03:00.610 --> 03:04.360
That's been drilled into us
 since we were juniors.

03:04.910 --> 03:11.690
I see. So, back then, you were 
trying to create a triangle with me.

03:11.690 --> 03:12.580
However...

03:13.670 --> 03:18.770
You initiated the move, but you didn't
 understand the concept of the triangle.

03:19.580 --> 03:22.380
You didn't even look at us.

03:23.020 --> 03:25.420
And all because you wanted to score.

03:26.280 --> 03:27.210
Isn't that right?

03:29.080 --> 03:34.360
Since we were out of options, I signaled 
for you to send the ball out to the wing.

03:35.340 --> 03:37.780
But you passed it back to me instead.

03:38.700 --> 03:42.060
And my pass got intercepted
 and they countered.

03:42.870 --> 03:44.170
You could've told me...

03:44.170 --> 03:45.150
I did.

03:45.150 --> 03:46.080
Huh?

03:46.460 --> 03:47.670
I did tell you.

03:48.890 --> 03:54.220
We always talk about the importance of
 triangles in our daily training sessions.

03:54.920 --> 03:57.530
You must've heard it said plenty of times.

03:59.460 --> 04:05.010
Maybe you thought it was too simple and 
didn't think any more on it. Or just maybe...

04:05.780 --> 04:07.970
...you weren't interested to begin with.

04:09.320 --> 04:11.110
If so, we had no chance.

04:11.810 --> 04:17.980
Even if we'd laid it all out for you, 
I doubt it would've stuck.

04:20.970 --> 04:24.200
For us promoted players, 
who clawed our way up to get here,

04:24.200 --> 04:28.490
your attitude is impossible to understand, 
and frankly, we didn't want to.

04:29.530 --> 04:30.900
I'm pathetic.

04:32.140 --> 04:36.250
Teach me how to play soccer!

04:37.620 --> 04:41.460
I was prepared to learn the 
game from scratch, but...

04:41.460 --> 04:49.140
It didn't even occur to me to learn
 from you guys. From my teammates.

04:51.140 --> 04:57.270
In this youth team, in order to get better,
 I need to absorb everything I see.

04:59.900 --> 05:02.900
Thank you, Asari and Kuroda.

05:03.290 --> 05:06.530
Thank you for teaching me soccer.

05:10.350 --> 05:11.890
But how'd you do it?

05:13.800 --> 05:16.050
How'd you improve so quickly?

05:16.900 --> 05:19.190
Okay! The game's restarting.

05:19.190 --> 05:20.670
Listen up, you guys!

05:20.670 --> 05:25.810
Those three there! If we can contain 
those three, their team won't function.

05:26.430 --> 05:29.580
We have a one-goal lead! 
Let's protect it with our lives!

05:39.180 --> 05:40.190
<i>All this time,</i>

05:40.910 --> 05:47.450
<i>I thought soccer was about carrying 
the ball at your feet towards the goal.</i>

05:47.890 --> 05:49.320
<i>But that's not it at all.</i>

05:50.490 --> 05:54.330
<i>You and two other players 
nearby form a triangle.</i>

05:54.750 --> 05:58.580
<i>So how do we slide this triangle into
 the opposition's part of the field?</i>

05:59.580 --> 06:06.090
<i>We tempt the other team towards us, 
and that creates a space. A tiny gap.</i>

06:07.810 --> 06:10.520
<i>One tip of the triangle
 sneaks into that gap.</i>

06:10.520 --> 06:17.100
<i>To put pressure on us and fill the space,
 other players come across to cover.</i>

06:18.600 --> 06:22.190
<i>Next, you pass the ball around the 
triangle to move the other team.</i>

06:22.750 --> 06:24.900
<i>The tiny gaps start to accumulate...</i>

06:25.380 --> 06:27.740
<i>And create a big space
in the opposition's half!</i>

06:29.610 --> 06:31.120
Dammit!

06:31.120 --> 06:34.720
<i>A-Amazing. This is amazing!</i>

06:34.720 --> 06:38.870
<i>If we keep this up, 
how many goals can we score?</i>

06:49.910 --> 06:53.530
<i>What... What is this?</i>

07:05.730 --> 07:07.440
Don't lose your man!

07:09.770 --> 07:10.700
Asari!

07:32.370 --> 07:34.380
Ah, I knew it.

07:35.420 --> 07:39.930
Everyone moved the way 
I envisioned they would.

07:45.460 --> 07:46.940
Esperion B

07:45.460 --> 07:46.940
Seikyo High

08:01.340 --> 08:04.580
He rebuilt the triangle.

08:04.580 --> 08:06.700
Anri? Yuma?

08:07.720 --> 08:13.830
He replaced Kuroda with Ohtomo
 as one tip of the triangle.

08:13.830 --> 08:16.470
Yup. It sure was somethin'.

08:18.340 --> 08:19.390
Ashito.

08:23.080 --> 08:27.900
That was weird. I... feel weird.

08:29.070 --> 08:37.160
It's like... I could see what they would all...
everyone on our team and theirs...

08:40.940 --> 08:45.620
I could see... what they would all do next.

08:48.630 --> 08:52.060
Ashito did great with that goal just now.

08:52.930 --> 08:55.710
But it was Asari and Ohtomo 
who combined to score.

08:56.890 --> 09:02.230
Aoi made a dummy run from
 left to right across the area,

09:02.230 --> 09:05.270
as if the final pass from
 Asari was going to him.

09:06.450 --> 09:11.280
Seikyo High was wariest of 
the three on the left wing,

09:11.280 --> 09:14.440
so they sent two players
 across to challenge him.

09:14.800 --> 09:24.790
Ashito

09:15.510 --> 09:17.220
But that was his plan.

09:16.800 --> 09:24.790
Move 
this guy

09:17.690 --> 09:22.970
He lured those players towards him
 to clear a path for Ohtomo's shot.

09:18.800 --> 09:24.790
Ohtomo

09:24.070 --> 09:29.790
On top of that, in order to draw 
Asari's attention to Ohtomo,

09:30.210 --> 09:35.800
he guided Asari's eyes to
 Ohtomo as he ran past him.

09:36.670 --> 09:39.680
It was subtle, but he pointed to him.

09:41.080 --> 09:44.930
It's true. That boy controlled everything.

09:45.450 --> 09:50.330
Just in this match alone, he's not only 
grasped the concept of triangles in soccer,

09:50.330 --> 09:52.280
he's built on it.

09:53.550 --> 09:57.450
But how is that even possible?

10:04.760 --> 10:07.710
We're in extra time! Last three minutes!

10:08.040 --> 10:11.340
Wrench 'em open! Score one
 more goal and we win!

10:11.340 --> 10:16.090
Protect the goal! Even if we have to rough 
'em up, we gotta keep the score tied!

10:21.460 --> 10:25.350
When they started squabblin' 
the day of the entrance ceremony,

10:25.610 --> 10:29.100
Ashito drew somethin' 
strange on the blackboard.

10:29.690 --> 10:33.900
